Content: Hi. Just logged onto my Agma wallet for first time in a few months and for whatever reason it's unable to reach the server. I went to settings and SPV and tried changing server and i continued getting the unreachable error message. Any ideas?

Content: update it, the SPV servers changed

Content: thanks

Author: kBone#9115
Content: When I get to the re installation detected do I leave the settings alone, and allow it to uninstall but don't delete any info?

Author: PTYX#6840
Content: I usually delete all app binaries but don't delete any wallet files

Author: PTYX#6840
Content: If you are using native always backup the wallet.dat before updating

Author: kBone#9115
Content: the 2 options are user data and zcash params do I want to delete those? Either way I am uninstalling correct?

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: @kBone Just choose "Re-install current version", those options are active only for "Uninstall" option

Author: kBone#9115
Content: thanks

Author: TonyL#3577
Content:
Be sure that you made a backup of wallet.dat in case of native mode usage (location of wallet.dat in different OS: https://komodoplatform.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/KPSD/pages/192675854/Location+of+Wallet.dat+File) 
And control your seed in case of SPV mode usage

Author: kBone#9115
Content: Thank you. So when it asks if i want to " uninstall agama and all it modules?" I say no?

Author: kBone#9115
Content: @TonyL

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: @kBone You have to press "Yes" because installer first uninstall old version and then installation package will install the new one

Author: kBone#9115
Content: ok

Author: kBone#9115
Content: worked well. Thanks for info

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: @kBone You're most welcome! :)
